PMI does not undertake to update any forward-looking statement that we may make from time to time, except in the normal course of its public disclosure obligations.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:1pt;text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-bottom:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Philip Morris International&#58; Delivering a Smoke-Free Future</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:1pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">Philip Morris International (PMI) is a leading international tobacco company working to deliver a smoke-free future and evolving its portfolio for the long term to include products outside of the tobacco and nicotine sector. The company&#8217;s current product portfolio primarily consists of cigarettes and smoke-free products, including heat-not-burn, vapor and oral nicotine products, which are sold in markets outside the U.S. Since 2008, PMI has invested more than USD 9 billion to develop, scientifically substantiate and commercialize innovative smoke-free products for adults who would otherwise continue to smoke, with the goal of completely ending the sale of cigarettes. This includes the </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:0.01pt;text-align:justify"><font><br></font></div><div style="height:61.92pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:right"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">2</font></div><div><font><br></font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:61.92pt;width:100%"><div><table style="border-collapse:collapse;display:inline-table;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:99.911%"><tr><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:32.233%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:32.233%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:32.234%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td></tr><tr style="height:15pt"><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td></tr></table></div><div><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-bottom:0.01pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">building of world-class scientific assessment capabilities, notably in the areas of pre-clinical systems toxicology, clinical and behavioral research, as well as post-market studies. The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has authorized the marketing of versions of PMI&#8217;s </font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">IQOS</font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> Platform 1 devices and consumables as Modified Risk Tobacco Products (MRTPs), finding that exposure modification orders for these products are appropriate to promote the public health. As of March 31, 2022, PMI's smoke-free products are available for sale in 71 markets, and PMI estimates that approximately 12.7 million adults around the world excluding Russia and Ukraine, have already switched to </font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">IQOS</font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> and stopped smoking. With a strong foundation and significant expertise in life sciences, in February 2021 PMI announced its ambition to expand into wellness and healthcare areas and deliver innovative products and solutions that aim to address unmet consumer and patient needs. For more information, please visit </font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%;text-decoration:underline">www.pmi.com</font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%"> and </font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%;text-decoration:underline">www.pmiscience.com</font><font style="color:#333333;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:151%">.</font></div><div style="height:61.92pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:right"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Calibri',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">3</font></div><div><font><br></font></div></div></div></body></html>

<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">5 Glossary of Key Terms and Definitions Glossary: General Terms  &#8226; &quot;PMI&quot; refers to Philip Morris International Inc. and its subsidiaries. Trademarks and service marks that are the registered property of, or licensed by, the subsidiaries of PMI, are italicized &#8226; Until March 28, 2008, PMI was a wholly owned subsidiary of Altria Group, Inc. (&quot;Altria&quot;). Since that time the company has been independent and is listed on the New York Stock Exchange (ticker symbol &quot;PM&quot;) &#8226; Comparisons are made to the same prior-year period unless otherwise stated &#8226; Unless otherwise stated, references to total industry, total market, PMI shipment volume and PMI market share performance reflect cigarettes and heated tobacco units &#8226; As of the first quarter of 2022, total industry volume, PMI in-market sales volume and PMI market share for the following geographies include the cigarillo category in Japan: the total international market, East Asia &amp; Australia Region, and Japanese domestic market &#8226; References to total international market, defined as worldwide cigarette and heated tobacco unit volume excluding the U.S., total industry, total market and market shares are PMI estimates for tax-paid products based on the latest available data from a number of internal and external sources and may, in defined instances, exclude the People's Republic of China and/or PMI's duty free business &#8226; 2021 and 2022 estimates for total industry volume and market share in certain geographies reflect limitations on the availability and accuracy of industry data during pandemic-related restrictions &#8226; &quot;OTP&quot; is defined as &quot;other tobacco products,&quot; primarily roll-your-own and make-your-own cigarettes, pipe tobacco, cigars and cigarillos, and does not include reduced-risk products &#8226; &quot;Combustible products&quot; is the term PMI uses to refer to cigarettes and OTP, combined &#8226; In-market sales, or &quot;IMS,&quot; is defined as sales to the retail channel, depending on the market and distribution model &#8226; &quot;Total shipment volume&quot; is defined as the combined total of cigarette shipment volume and heated tobacco unit shipment volume &#8226; Following the acquisitions of Fertin Pharma A/S, OtiTopic, Inc. and Vectura Group plc., PMI added the &quot;Other&quot; category in the third quarter of 2021. Business operations for the Other category are evaluated separately from the geographical operating segments &#8226; &quot;RBH&quot; refers to PMI&#8217;s Canadian subsidiary, Rothmans, Benson &amp; Hedges Inc. &#8226; The Companies&#8217; Creditors Arrangement Act (CCAA) is a Canadian federal law that permits a Canadian business to restructure its affairs while carrying on its business in the ordinary course 6 </FONT></DIV>

<DIV style="page-break-before:always;">&nbsp;</DIV>

<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">Glossary: General Terms (cont.) &#8226; &quot;EU&quot; is defined as the European Union Region &#8226; &quot;EE&quot; is defined as the Eastern Europe Region &#8226; &quot;ME&amp;A&quot; is defined as the Middle East &amp; Africa Region and includes PMI's duty free business &#8226; &quot;S&amp;SA&quot; is defined as the South &amp; Southeast Asia Region &#8226; &quot;EA&amp;A&quot; is defined as the East Asia &amp; Australia Region &#8226; &#8220;AMCS&#8221; is defined as the Americas Region. It refers to the former Latin America &amp; Canada segment, which was renamed as the Americas segment as of the third quarter of 2021. References to &quot;Americas&quot; may, in defined instances, exclude the U.S. &#8226; Following the deconsolidation of PMI's Canadian subsidiary, Rothmans, Benson &amp; Hedges, Inc. (RBH), PMI will continue to report the volume of brands sold by RBH for which other PMI subsidiaries are the trademark owner. These include HEETS, Next, Philip Morris and Rooftop &#8226; From time to time, PMI&#8217;s shipment volumes are subject to the impact of distributor inventory movements, and estimated total industry/market volumes are subject to the impact of inventory movements in various trade channels that include estimated trade inventory movements of PMI&#8217;s competitors arising from market-specific factors that significantly distort reported volume disclosures. Such factors may include changes to the manufacturing supply chain, shipment methods, consumer demand, timing of excise tax increases or other influences that may affect the timing of sales to customers. In such instances, in addition to reviewing PMI shipment volumes and certain estimated total industry/market volumes on a reported basis, management reviews these measures on an adjusted basis that excludes the impact of distributor and/or estimated trade inventory movements. Management also believes that disclosing PMI shipment volumes and estimated total industry/market volumes in such circumstances on a basis that excludes the impact of distributor and/or estimated trade inventory movements, such as on an IMS basis, improves the comparability of performance and trends for these measures over different reporting periods &#8226; &quot;ESG&quot; stands for environmental, social, and governance &#8226; &quot;Illicit trade&quot; refers to domestic non-tax paid products &#8226; &quot;SoM&quot; stands for share of market 7 Glossary: Financial Terms  &#8226; Net revenues related to combustible products refer to the operating revenues generated from the sale of these products, including shipping and handling charges billed to customers, net of sales and promotion incentives, and excise taxes. PMI recognizes revenue when control is transferred to the customer, typically either upon shipment or delivery of goods &#8226; Net revenues related to RRPs represent the sale of heated tobacco units, heat-not-burn devices and related accessories, and other nicotine-containing products, primarily e-vapor and oral nicotine products, including shipping and handling charges billed to customers, net of sales and promotion incentives, and excise taxes. PMI recognizes revenue when control is transferred to the customer, typically either upon shipment or delivery of goods &#8226; Net revenues in the Other category primarily consist of operating revenues generated from the sale of inhaled therapeutics, and oral and intra-oral delivery systems, that are included in the operating results of PMI&#8217;s new Wellness and Healthcare business, Vectura Fertin Pharma &#8226; Adjusted net revenues exclude the impact related to the Saudi Arabia customs assessments &#8226; &#8220;COGS&#8220; stands for Cost Of Goods Sold &#8226; &quot;SG&amp;A&quot; stands for selling, general &amp; administrative &#8226; &quot;Adjusted Operating Income (OI) Margin&quot; is calculated as adjusted OI, divided by adjusted net revenues &#8226; &quot;Net debt&quot; is defined as total debt, less cash and cash equivalents &#8226; Growth rates presented on an organic basis for consolidated financial results reflect currency-neutral underlying results &#8226; Management reviews net revenues, operating income, operating income margin, operating cash flow and earnings per share, or &quot;EPS,&quot; on an adjusted basis, which may exclude the impact of currency and other items such as acquisitions, asset impairment and exit costs, tax items and other special items. Currency-neutral and organic growth rates reflect the way management views underlying performance for these measures. PMI believes that such measures provide useful insight into underlying business trends and results. Management reviews these measures because they exclude changes in currency exchange rates and other factors that may distort underlying business trends, thereby improving the comparability of PMI&#8217;s business performance between reporting periods. Furthermore, PMI uses several of these measures in its management compensation program to promote internal fairness and a disciplined assessment of performance against company targets. PMI discloses these measures to enable investors to view the business through the eyes of management &#8226; &quot;Fair value adjustment for equity security investments&quot; reflects the adjustment resulting from share price movements in passive investments for publicly traded entities that are not controlled or influenced by PMI. Under U.S. GAAP, such adjustments are required, since January 1, 2018, to be reflected directly in the income statement 8 </FONT></DIV>

<DIV><FONT size="1" style="font-size:1pt;color:white">Glossary: Reduced-Risk Products &#8226; Reduced-risk products (&#8220;RRPs&#8221;) is the term PMI uses to refer to products that present, are likely to present, or have the potential to present less risk of harm to smokers who switch to these products versus continuing smoking. PMI has a range of RRPs in various stages of development, scientific assessment and commercialization. PMI's RRPs are smoke-free products that contain and/or generate far lower quantities of harmful and potentially harmful constituents than found in cigarette smoke &#8226; &quot;Aerosol&quot; refers to a gaseous suspension of fine solid particles and/or liquid droplets &#8226; &quot;Combustion&quot; is the process of burning a substance in oxygen, producing heat and often light &#8226; &quot;Smoke&quot; is a visible suspension of solid particles, liquid droplets and gases in air, emitted when a material burns &#8226; &quot;Heated tobacco units,&quot; or &quot;HTUs,&quot; is the term PMI uses to refer to heated tobacco consumables, which include the company's HEETS, HEETS Creations, HEETS Dimensions, HEETS Marlboro and HEETS FROM MARLBORO (defined collectively as HEETS), Marlboro Dimensions, Marlboro HeatSticks, Parliament HeatSticks and TEREA, as well as the KT&amp;G-licensed brands, Fiit and Miix (outside of South Korea) &#8226; IQOS heat-not-burn devices are precisely controlled heating devices into which a specially designed and proprietary tobacco units are inserted and heated to generate an aerosol &#8226; &quot;PMI heat-not-burn products&quot; include licensed KT&amp;G heat-not-burn products &#8226; &quot;PMI HTUs&quot; include licensed KT&amp;G HTUs &#8226; HTU &quot;offtake volume&quot; represents the estimated retail offtake of HTUs based on a selection of sales channels that vary by market, but notably include retail points of sale and e-commerce platforms &#8226; HTU &quot;offtake share&quot; represents the estimated retail offtake volume of HTUs divided by the sum of estimated total offtake volume for cigarettes and HTUs &#8226; Market share for HTUs is defined as the total sales volume for HTUs as a percentage of the total estimated sales volume for cigarettes and HTUs 9 Glossary: Reduced-Risk Products (cont.) &#8226; &quot;Total IQOS users&quot; is defined as the estimated number of Legal Age (minimum 18 years) users of PMI heat-not-burn products, for which PMI HTUs represented at least a portion of their daily tobacco consumption over the past seven days The estimated number of adults who have &quot;switched to IQOS and stopped smoking&quot; reflects:&#9148; for markets where there are no heat-not-burn products other than PMI heat-not-burn products: daily individual consumption of PMI HTUs represents the totality of their daily tobacco consumption in the past seven days&#9148; for markets where PMI heat-not-burn products are among other heat-not-burn products: daily individual consumption of HTUs represents the totality of their daily tobacco consumption in the past seven days, of which at least 70% is PMI HTUs. Note: The above IQOS user metrics reflect PMI estimates, which are based on consumer claims and sample-based statistical assessments with an average margin of error of +/-5% at a 95% Confidence Interval in key volume markets. The accuracy and reliability of IQOS user metrics may vary based on individual market maturity and availability of information As of December 2020, PMI heat-not-burn products and HTUs include licensed KT&amp;G heat-not-burn products and HTUs, respectively &#8226; &quot;FDA&quot; stands for the U.S. Food &amp; Drug Administration &#8226; &quot;MRTP&quot; stands for Modified Risk Tobacco Product, the term used by the U.S. FDA to refer to RRPs &#8226; &quot;MRTP application&quot; stands for Modified Risk Tobacco Product application under section 911 of the FD&amp;C Act &#8226; &quot;PMTA&quot; stands for Premarket Tobacco Application under section 910 of the FD&amp;C Act &#8226; &quot;Acquisition&quot; refers to our efforts to switch LAS from smoking cigarettes to RRPs or to switch LAU from competing smoke-free products to PMI&#8217;s RRPs &#8226; &quot;Retention&quot; refers to our efforts to deter LAU from going back to smoking cigarettes or from choosing a competing smoke-free product instead of a PMI RRP 10 </FONT></DIV>
<P><HR noshade><P>
<DIV style="page-break-before:always;">&nbsp;</DIV>

// Edgar(tm) Renderer was created by staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Data and content created by government employees within the scope of their employment are not subject to domestic copyright protection. 17 U.S.C. 105.
var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}

/* Updated 2009-11-04 */
